claim.claim-text:
1. An exercise scooter configured for standup operation comprising: 
a frame, said frame capable of supporting a user; 
a first wheel, said first wheel in contact with the ground and operably associated with said frame for steering said exercise scooter; 
a second wheel, said second wheel rotatably connected to said frame and in contact with said ground; 
a crank, said crank positioned adjacent said second wheel and rotatably connected to said frame protruding on either side; 
a drive coupling, said drive coupling operably associated with said crank and said second wheel; 
a pair of guides, said guide operably associated with said frame positioned adjacent said first wheel; 
a pair of foot support members having foot engaging pedals, said foot support member pivotally connected to said crank and operably associated with said guide to predetermine the angular position of said foot support member for each position of said crank; 
said pedal configured to move relative to said frame when the foot of said user is rotating said crank whereby said crank causes rotation of said second wheel to propel said exercise scooter.

13. A scooter for user propulsion comprising: 
at least two wheels, said wheels in contact with the ground to support said scooter; 
a frame, said frame configured to connect said wheels and support a user; 
a pair of pedals stabilized for user support, said pedals operably associated with said frame for both up and down as well as back and forth movement, and having a predetermined pedal angle for each foot position; 
said pedal configured to move relative to said frame when the foot of said user exerts force upon said pedal whereby said pedal movement causes rotation of said wheels while the heel of said foot generally maintains contact with said pedal during said movement.

22. A method of exercising on a scooter of the type having a frame supported by a pair of wheels, a handlebar to steer one of the wheels, left and right cranks supported by the frame and rotatable relative thereto about a common crank axis positioned adjacent the other wheel, and left and right foot supporting members having respective intermediate portions pivotally connected to respective cranks and respective ends supported by a right and left guide positioned adjacent the steering wheel to the frame in reciprocal fashion relative thereto, wherein rotation of the cranks is linked to propulsion of a wheel, comprising the steps of: 
standing with a respective foot on each foot supporting member; 
steering one of the wheels with the handlebar; 
moving the foot supporting members through a closed loop arcuate path to propel the other wheel; 
moving the scooter relative to the ground.
